Definition.WordDefinition: Cheesy \Chees"y\, a. Having the nature, qualities, taste, form, consistency, or appearance of cheese. [1913 Webster]
cheesy adj : of very poor quality [syn: {bum}, {cheap}, {chintzy}, {crummy}, {punk}, {sleazy}, {tinny}] [also: {cheesiest}, {cheesier}]
